  "prompt": "Who is the best mobile in 2016?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" mobile phone of 2016 depends on various factors such as design, performance, camera quality, operating system, and personal preferences. However, several flagship smartphones released in 2016 were widely acclaimed and stood out in the market:\n\n1. **Apple iPhone 7 and iPhone 7 Plus**\n   - **Highlights**:\n     - **Design**: Sleek aluminum bodies available in multiple colors.\n     - **Performance**: Powered by the A10 Fusion chip, offering smooth performance.\n     - **Camera**: The iPhone 7 Plus introduced a dual-camera system, enabling better photos and optical zoom.\n     - **Other Features**: Removal of the headphone jack was a controversial but notable change, along with improved water resistance.\n\n2. **Samsung Galaxy S7 and Galaxy S7 Edge**\n   - **Highlights**:\n     - **Design**: Premium build with a choice between a flat (S7) and curved (S7 Edge) display.\n     - **Display**: Super AMOLED displays with vibrant colors and deep blacks.\n     - **Camera**: Excellent camera performance, especially in low-light conditions.\n     - **Battery and Storage**: Removable battery and expandable storage were appreciated by many users.\n\n3. **Google Pixel and Pixel XL**\n   - **Highlights**:\n     - **Camera**: Widely praised for having one of the best smartphone cameras, especially for still photography.\n     - **Software**: Stock Android experience with timely updates directly from Google.\n     - **Performance**: Smooth and efficient performance, though the battery life received mixed reviews.\n     - **Design**: Simple and understated design, focusing more on functionality.\n\n4. **OnePlus 3**\n   - **Highlights**:\n     - **Performance**: High-end specifications at a relatively affordable price point.\n     - **Design**: Premium build quality with a stylish appearance.\n     - **Software**: OxygenOS offered a clean and customizable Android experience.\n     - **Battery**: Decent battery life and fast charging capabilities.\n\n5. **LG V20**\n   - **Highlights**:\n     - **Audio**: Dual DAC for superior sound quality, appealing to audiophiles.\n     - **Camera**: Competent camera performance with manual controls.\n     - **Display**: Large, vibrant display suitable for media consumption.\n     - **Battery**: Removable battery and good battery life.\n\n**Honorable Mentions**:\n- **Sony Xperia Z5 Premium**: Known for its stunning 4K display.\n- **HTC 10**: Appreciated for its design and front-facing camera, ideal for selfies.\n\n**Conclusion**:\nWhile there wasn\u2019t a single \"best\" mobile phone in 2016, the **Samsung Galaxy S7/S7 Edge** and **Apple iPhone 7 series** were often at the top of the list due to their overall performance, design, and feature sets. The **Google Pixel** also garnered significant praise, particularly for its camera and software experience. Ultimately, the best choice depended on the user's specific needs and preferences, such as whether they preferred iOS or Android, camera quality, design aesthetics, or other features.",
